==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Darrain
<hw>Dar"rain</hw>, }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>deraisnier</ets> to explain, defend, to
maintain in legal action by proof and reasonings, LL.
<ets>derationare</ets>; <ets>de-</ets> + <ets>rationare</ets> to
discourse, contend in law, fr. L. <ets>ratio</ets> reason, in LL., legal
cause. Cf. <er>Arraign</er>, and see <er>Reason</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To make ready to fight; to array.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Darrain</qex> your battle, for they are at hand.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fight out; to contest; to decide by combat.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧To <xex>darrain</xex> the battle.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer .</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Darrein</ent>⟦br⟧
